The so-called rules came from a long ago outdated time, prior to this century, from a time when men owned their females like livestock. A man's son would carry on the family name, the family business or land. But a female would be good only to produce heirs and raise the progeny.<br>
We live in a time where it takes two incomes to create a stable home, where most single income families are mothers raising the children and providing the economic base. This double standard myth is antiquated and ridiculous, and our young women need to wake up and take control of their destinies instead of buying into the myth.
